The paper deals with manifold learning applied to medical imaging problems, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) research. The proposed method involves solving a convex optimization problem, which is a common topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) research. The method also involves controlling the sparsity of the resulting interpolation function, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) research.
